r learning --> <!-- BEGIN Academic scores by country - field: adm-reqs-by-country --> <!-- END Academic scores by country --> <!-- END MS edits --> <p class="mt-5" id="course-require" style="font-weight:bold;">Course requirements</p> <p> To be eligible to receive the Bachelor of Health and Human Science (Honours) students must complete the equivalent of 8 units (96 credit points).</p> <p> <strong>Class of Honours </strong></p> <p> This degree may be awarded in the following classes:<br/> 1. First Class;<br/> 2. Second Class (Division 1);<br/> 3. Second Class (Division 2); or<br/> 4. Third Class.</p> <p> Students are required to satisfy requirements for the coursework units and Honours Class will be determined from the grades in the thesis units.</p> <p class="mt-5" style="font-weight:bold;">Other things to consider</p> <div class="accordion accordion-flush" id="accordionRequirements"> <div class="accordion-item"> <p class="accordion-header" id="agenda-heading480173" style="font-weight:bold;"> <button aria-controls="agenda-collapse480173" aria-expanded="true" class="accordion-button collapsed js-triggerRefresh" data-bs-target="#agenda-collapse480173" data-bs-toggle="collapse" type="button"> Credit and recognition of prior learning </button> </p> <div aria-labelledby="agenda-heading480173" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordionRequirements" id="agenda-collapse480173"> <div class="accordion-body"> <p>Credit for Prior Learning, also referred to as ‘Advanced Standing’ or Recognition for Prior Learning (RPL), is the process of looking at your prior study and/or experience to assess if you can be awarded academic credit or gain entry to a course on the basis of your existing knowledge and skills.</p> <p><a href="https://www.scu.edu.au/study/how-to-apply/credit-for-recognition-of-prior-learning/">Learn more</a></p> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>',
