dit points), and</li> <li> 4 electives (48 credit points)</li> </ul> <p> <br/> <strong>Honours Pathway</strong></p> <p> Students who have completed the first 16 units (192 credit points) listed in the recommended course progression of the Bachelor of Social Work with a GPA of at least 5.0 will be invited to apply for consideration for transfer to the Bachelor of Social Work (Honours).</p> <p> <br/> <strong>Work Integrated Learning</strong></p> <p> This course includes work integrated learning. Pre-requisites to meet national and state-based regulatory requirements, as detailed on the <a href="https://www.scu.edu.au/health/work-integrated-learning/">Faculty of Health Work Integrated Learning page</a> must be met prior to work integrated learning. All work integrated learning hours must be completed and professional behaviour and conduct must be demonstrated.</p> <p> <br/> <strong>Inherent Requirements</strong></p> <p> Inherent Requirements apply to this course as defined on the <a href="http://www.scu.edu.au/ir/">Student Equity and Inclusion website</a>. Students who have a disability or health condition which may impact on their ability to meet these requirements are encouraged to visit the Student Equity and Inclusion website for further information and contact details.</p> <p class="mt-5" style="font-weight:bold;">Other things to consider</p> <div class="accordion accordion-flush" id="accordionRequirements"> <div class="accordion-item"> <p class="accordion-header" id="agenda-heading539495" style="font-weight:bold;"> <button aria-controls="agenda-collapse539495" aria-expanded="true" class="accordion-button collapsed js-triggerRefresh" data-bs-target="#agenda-collapse539495" data-bs-toggle="collapse" type="button"> Admissions Transparency </button> </p> <div aria-labelledby="agenda-heading539495" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordionRequirements" id="agenda-collapse539495"> <div class="accordion-body"> <p>As part of our commitment to admissi